      "content": "<hr />\n<p><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">Fortune recently released its annual Great Place to Work survey.</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">According to Fortune, nearly half a million employees <a href=\"http://fortune.com/best-workplaces-for-diversity\">completed</a> surveys about their workplace and diversity and inclusion.  </span><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">Delta <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Delta/status/806246383447580673\">was</a> the only airline for the 50 Best Companies for Diversity and 10 Best Companies for African-Americans. Kimpton Hotels &amp; Restaurants and Marriott International ranked highly and were the two hotel companies included in the top 10.</span></p>\n<p>Overall, the companies that ranked highly had impressive diversity statistics. <span style=\"font-weight:400;\">At Raines International, we’d like to highlight the top 10 companies and note their high representation of diverse executives and staff. Below are the top 10 Best Companies for Diversity, with their breakdowns of executives and workforce.</span></p>\n<ol>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">Texas Health Resources: 60% women executives, 14% minority executives, 18% African-American/Black, 11% Asian, 12% Hispanic/Latino</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">Delta: 15% women executives, 19% minority executives, 21% African-American/Black, 8% Asian, 9% Hispanic/Latino</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">Navy Federal Credit Union: 47% women executives, 28% minority executives, 20% African-American/Black, 11% Asian, 9% Hispanic/Latino</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">Kimpton Hotels &amp; Restaurants: 29% women executives, 4% minority executives, 18% African-American/Black, 7% Asian, 35% Hispanic/Latino</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">Ultimate Software: 32% women executives, 8% minority executives, 12% African-American/Black, 8% Asian, 19% Hispanic/Latino</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">Miami Children’s Health System: 43% women executives, 43% minority executives, 10% African-American/Black, 4% Asian, 64% Hispanic/Latino</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">Marriott International: 34% women executives, 15% minority executives, 22% African-American/Black, 10% Asian, 29% Hispanic/Latino</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">Build-a-Bear Workshop: 50% women executives, 6% minority executives, 11% African-American/Black, 2% Asian, 17% Hispanic/Latino</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">Quicken Loans 34% women executives, 9% minority executives, 19% African American/Black, 4% Asian, 5% Hispanic/Latino</span></li>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">USAA:</span><span style=\"font-weight:400;\"> 32% women executives, 20% minority executives, 9% African-American/Black, 3% Asian, 31% Hispanic/Latino</span></li>\n</ol>\n<p><span style=\"font-weight:400;\">Fortune also broke down the best workplaces for different ethnicities:</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li><span style=\"font-weight:400;\"><a href=\"http://fortune.com/2016/12/05/best-workplaces-diversity-asian-americans/\">10 Best Workplaces for Asians</a>, with IT company Katalyst Technologies topped the list with 90% Asian representation</span></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://fortune.com/2016/12/05/best-workplaces-diversity-hispanics-latinos/\">10 Best Workplaces for Hispanics/Latinos</a> with Miami’ Children’s Health System, which has 64% Latino representation, ranking first</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://fortune.com/2016/12/05/best-workplaces-diversity-african-americans/\">10 Best Workplaces for African-Americans</a> with Methodist Le Bonheur Healthcare earning the top stop with 41% representation</li>\n</ul>\n<hr />\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n",
