      "date": "2016-12-09T10:33:57-05:00",
      "modified": "2016-12-09T10:47:27-05:00",
      "title": "What We&#8217;re Reading: Dec. 9 Edition",
      "URL": "https://rainesinternational.wordpress.com/2016/12/09/what-were-reading-dec-9-edition/",
      "short_URL": "http://wp.me/p7C5yw-2yO",
      "content": "<p><em>Below is Raines Perspectives’ weekly curation of interesting reads about business, careers, hiring and more. Send suggestions to perspectives@rainesinternational.com.</em></p>\n<p>1. Dow Jones&#8217;s Chief People Officer Mark Musgrave revealed that a study of Dow Jones&#8217; compensation found that there is no difference in pay for different genders and ethnicities. Read: <a href=\"http://talkingbiznews.com/1/dow-jones-salaries-dont-vary-due-to-gender-or-ethnicity/\">&#8220;Dow Jones: Salaries don&#8217;t vary due to gender or ethnicity.&#8221;</a></p>\n<p>2. Start-up co-founder and CEO Joshua Reeves of Gusto explained to the Wall Street Journal&#8217;s Rachel Feintzeig his new project shadowing members of Gusto&#8217;s 37 teams so he best understands how the company is working at a larger scale, from top to bottom. Read &#8220;<a href=\"http://www.wsj.com/articles/ceo-shadows-workers-to-learn-nitty-gritty-details-1480424402\">CEO Shadows Workers to Learn &#8216;Nitty-Gritty&#8217; Details.&#8221;</a></p>\n<p>3. Harvard Business Review recently looked at gender-diverse coaching. Read &#8220;<a href=\"https://hbr.org/2016/12/men-can-improve-how-they-mentor-women-heres-how?utm_source=twitter&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_campaign=harvardbiz\">Men can improve how they mentor women. Here&#8217;s how.&#8221;</a></p>\n<p>4. UPS celebrated its perfect score on the Human Rights Campaign&#8217;s Corporate Equality Index and was named a Best Place to Work for LGBT Equality. Read <a href=\"https://www.pressroom.ups.com/pressroom/ContentDetailsViewer.page?ConceptType=PressReleases&amp;id=1480952529320-972\">the press release.</a></p>\n<p>5. The Wall Street Journal published a video from its CEO Council conference and Fuqua School of Business professor John Graham&#8217;s advice on evaluating CEOs. Watch<a href=\"http://www.wsj.com/articles/john-graham-on-evaluating-ceos-1479783841\"> the brief video</a> below.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/iframe.html?guid=E84D7B21-409A-4603-8206-696F827E0DE7\">http://video-api.wsj.com/api-video/player/iframe.html?guid=E84D7B21-409A-4603-8206-696F827E0DE7</a></p>\n<p>6. And of course, we recommend you check out Raines Perspectives&#8217; latest piece on better networking. Read <a href=\"http://perspectives.rainesinternational.com/article/9699-5-Tips-for-Better-Networking\">&#8220;5 Tips for Better Networking.&#8221;</a></p>\n<p><em>Recommendations? Feedback? E-mail us at perspectives@rainesinternational.com</em></p>\n",
