      "short_URL": "http://wp.me/p7C5yw-27o",
      "content": "<p>Received a B.S. in Managerial Economics from the <strong>University of California, Davis</strong>. Following graduation stepped into a number of leadership roles at various non-profit organizations, creating and leading core program strategies.</p>\n<p>Worked as a Consultant at a management consulting firm in their consumer and retail division before obtaining his <strong>MBA</strong> from <strong>Duke University’s Fuqua School of Business</strong>.</p>\n<p>Joined a <strong>top-tier management consulting firm</strong>, where he specialized in the consumer and retail industries and worked on brand strategy, consumer insights and business development engagements. Spent a year in Paris as a corporate ambassador, working with clients across Europe.</p>\n<p>Most recently, was <strong>recruited by Raines International</strong> to serve as <strong>Director of Strategy</strong> at a <strong>Fortune 500 Retail Company</strong>. Works with key senior executives to set the overall strategic priorities of the Company, supporting the development of long-term merchandising initiatives that address the major merchandise issues it is likely to face as it continues to grow.</p>\n",
