      "short_URL": "http://wp.me/p7C5yw-28H",
      "content": "<p style=\"text-align:left;\">Received a <strong>B.A and M.S.</strong> in <strong>Mechanical Engineering</strong>, and an <strong>M.S</strong> in <strong>Computer Science</strong>. Joined a <strong>Fortune 100 Electronic Manufacturing Company</strong> as a Senior Research Engineer. Left to obtain his <strong>MBA</strong> from <strong>The University of Chicago’s Booth School of Business</strong>.</p>\n<p>After graduation, joined a <strong>top-tier management consulting firm</strong> as an Associate, where he consulted on strategic and operational issues for high-tech, consumer electronics and retail industries.</p>\n<p>Left the firm after five years as a Manager to join a <strong>Fortune 100 Information Technology Company</strong> as a <strong>Director of Corporate Strategy.</strong> Over a fourteen year tenure with the Company, served in various senior Strategy, Marketing, and Sales roles, such as <strong>Vice President, Strategy &amp; Business Transformation, Vice President, Geographic Expansion &amp; Growth Market</strong>s,<a href=\"https://www.linkedin.com/title/vice-president%2C-geographic-expansion%2C-ibm-growth-markets%2C-shanghai%2C-china?trk=mprofile_title\"><strong> </strong></a>and most recently, <strong>Vice President, Sales, Systems &amp; Technology Group.</strong></p>\n<p>Most recently served as <strong>Senior Vice President, Cloud Services </strong>at a <strong>Fortune 500 IT Solutions Company</strong>, where he developed and executed strategy to grow the Company’s Cloud line of business.</p>\n<p>Most recently, he has been <strong>recruited by Raines International</strong> to a <strong>Private Equity-owned Educational Technology Company</strong> to serve as <strong>Executive Vice President</strong>. In this role, is responsible for developing a strategic marketing plan to advance the Company’s mission and objectives and drive revenue growth.</p>\n",
