      "title": "Vice President, Strategy, Fortune 500 Retail Company",
      "URL": "https://rainesinternational.wordpress.com/2015/12/22/vice-president-strategy-fortune-500-retail-company/",
      "short_URL": "http://wp.me/p7C5yw-28J",
      "content": "<p>Received a <strong>Bachelor of Science </strong>degree in<strong> Business Administration</strong> from <strong>University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill</strong> and joined a <strong>Top-Tier Management Consulting Firm</strong> as an Associate Consultant. After three years with the Firm, attended <strong>Harvard School of Business</strong> and obtained an <strong>Master in Business </strong><b>Administration</b>.</p>\n<p>Returned to the Firm and joined the <strong>Consumer Goods and Retail Practice</strong>, leading a variety of initiatives involving Evaluated new market entry for major beverage company, and <strong>leadership, coaching and people development</strong>. Engagements included designing ground breaking digital organization for a <strong>Multi-banner Retailer</strong>, evaluating new market entry for a <strong>Multibillion-dollar Beverage Company</strong>, and  building a new organization to support digital growth to redefine the role of marketing at a major <strong>Beauty Company</strong>.</p>\n<p>Promoted to <strong>Principal</strong> and was responsible for structuring approaches to solve problems, managing executive client relationships, and supervising and developing over <strong>75 Managers, Consultants, and Associate Consultants</strong> throughout her tenure with the Firm.</p>\n<p><strong>Recruited by Raines International</strong> to serve as <strong>Vice President</strong><strong> of Strategy</strong> at a <strong>Fortune 500 Retail Company</strong>. Works with key senior executives to set the <strong>overall strategic priorities of the Company</strong>, supporting the development of long-term merchandising initiatives that address the major merchandise issues it is likely to face as it continues to grow.</p>\n<p><strong>Next Move?</strong><strong> </strong>Functional or Operational Leadership Role.</p>\n",
