      "title": "Director, Corporate &amp; Investment Banking Consulting, Multibillion-dollar Financial Services Company",
      "URL": "https://rainesinternational.wordpress.com/2015/10/06/director-corporate-investment-banking-consulting-multibillion-dollar-financial-services-company/",
      "short_URL": "http://wp.me/p7C5yw-28R",
      "content": "<p>Received a <strong>Master of Science</strong> in <strong>Aeronautical Engineering</strong> from the Imperial College, London in 2003. After graduation, joined a <strong>top-tier management consulting firm</strong>. While there, participated in financial services, social sector and duty free management consulting engagements in an analyst role.</p>\n<p>Received executive education from <strong>INSEAD, Paris</strong> and <strong>SDA Bocconi, Milano</strong> in<strong> financial accounting for managers</strong> and <strong>corporate finance </strong>respectively.</p>\n<p>Then spent six years at another <strong>top-tier management consulting firm</strong> as a <strong>Senior Engagement Manager</strong> in the <strong>Corporate and Investment Banking Practice</strong>. While there, projects involved <strong>mergers &amp; acquisitions, strategy and turnaround, start-up ventures</strong>, as well as others.</p>\n<p>Spent the last two years working at a <strong>leading global financial services firm. </strong>As <strong>Vice President </strong>of<strong> Corporate Strategy and Strategic Investments</strong> lead cross-LOB high profile projects for Executive Management and Board of Directors.</p>\n<p>Most recently, he has been <strong>recruited by Raines International</strong> to a <strong>Multi-Billion Dollar Financial Services</strong> <strong>Company </strong>to serve as <strong>Senior Director of Corporate &amp; Investment Banking Consulting</strong>. In this role, works directly with executive management on strategic projects, with access to the resources of a premier financial institution.</p>\n<p><strong>Next move?</strong> Broad spectrum of functional or general management opportunities</p>\n",
