      "title": "DVP, Inventory Management, Multibillion-dollar Retail Company",
      "URL": "https://rainesinternational.wordpress.com/2015/08/24/dvp-inventory-management-multibillion-dollar-retail-company/",
      "short_URL": "http://wp.me/p7C5yw-28U",
      "content": "<p>Received a <strong>BS</strong> and <strong>MS</strong> in Decision and Information Sciences followed by an <strong>MBA from The Kellogg School of Management at Northwestern University</strong>.</p>\n<p>Accepted to the <strong>Business Leadership Program</strong> of a <strong>Fortune 50 Retail Company</strong>. Following the program’s completion, served as an <strong>Inventory Merchant</strong> and later as <strong>Manager of Merchandising Operations</strong> at the Company, managing a team of analysts to redesign merchandising processes and support enterprise growth strategy for the Retailer.</p>\n<p>Joined a <strong>Top-Tier Management Consulting Firm</strong> as a Consultant. Over her seven year tenure with the Firm, was promoted to the <strong>Principal-level</strong>, leading, staffing and working in teams focused on corporate strategy, mergers &amp; acquisitions, strategic planning, and operational excellence for <strong>Fortune 500 clients</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Recruited by Raines International</strong> to serve <strong>Divisional Vice President of Inventory Management</strong> at a <strong>Multibillion-dollar</strong><strong> Retail Company</strong>. In this role, is responsible for leading the planning team in providing world class service to the Company’s retail stores while optimizing the management of inventory assets and delivering the merchandising sales and margin plans.</p>\n<p><strong>Next Move?</strong><strong> </strong>COO</p>\n",
