      "short_URL": "http://wp.me/p7C5yw-28W",
      "content": "<p>Received a <strong>Bachelor of Mechanical Engineering</strong> from <strong>Vanderbilt University</strong> and joined a top <strong>Management Consulting Firm</strong> as a Systems Analyst in the Firm’s <strong>Technology Integration Practice</strong>. Left the Firm as a Consultant and obtained an <strong>MBA</strong> from <strong>The Tuck School of Business at Dartmouth</strong>.</p>\n<p>Returned to the firm as a <strong>Senior Consultant in Strategy and Operations Practice</strong>, focusing on Supply Chain and Distribution engagements for Retail and Consumer clients. Projects included designing and implementing all operation processes for a <strong>$3M Supply Chain project</strong> for a Retail Client and benchmarking customer facing capabilities of a <strong>$13B Retail Consumer Electronics Company</strong> against its competitors in order to identify strategic opportunities.</p>\n<p>Later joined a <strong>Multibillion-dollar Retail Company as a Director of Import Operations</strong>. Over his four year tenure with the Retailer, held various senior Operations roles, such as <strong>Senior Director of International Logistics and Senior Director of International Supply Chain and Supply Chain Strategy</strong>. In these roles, was responsible for defining and leading the supply chain strategy/analytics function, developing a five year strategy that is currently being implemented by the Company’s supply chain teams.</p>\n<p><strong>Recruited by Raines International</strong> to serve as <strong>Senior Director of Strategy</strong> at a <strong>Fortune 500 Retail Company</strong>. Works with key senior executives to set the overall strategic priorities of the Company, supporting the development of long-term merchandising initiatives that address the major merchandise issues it is likely to face as it continues to grow.</p>\n<p><strong>Next Move?</strong><strong> </strong>Functional or Operational Leadership Role.</p>\n",
