      "title": "Vice President, Head of Commercial, Multibillion-dollar Energy Retailer",
      "URL": "https://rainesinternational.wordpress.com/2015/07/13/vice-president-head-of-commercial-multibillion-dollar-energy-retailer/",
      "short_URL": "http://wp.me/p7C5yw-28Z",
      "content": "<p>Obtained a Bachelor of Arts in Economics, followed by an <strong>MBA</strong> from The Fuqua School of Business at <strong>Duke University</strong>.</p>\n<p>Began his career as National Sales Manager at a Multi-Million Dollar Consumer Products Company, later founding an online retailer of home furnishings. Following business school joined a <strong>Top-Tier Management Consulting Firm</strong>, driving initiatives in sales, marketing, revenue growth, strategy and pricing within consumer products, services and logistics providers. Over his five year tenure with the firm, led multiple teams of strategy consultants serving <strong>Senior Management of Fortune 500 Companies</strong> in engagements that included developing strategy for the CEO of a <strong>Multi-Billion Dollar Logistics Provider</strong> and leading pricing and sales transformation at a <strong>Fortune 100 Industrial Company</strong>.</p>\n<p>As an <strong>Associate Principal</strong>, moved to a <strong>Fortune 50 Media and Technology Company</strong>. Served as <strong>Vice President, Sales Development</strong>, where it was responsible for driving continual performance improvement across all sales channels and all divisions/regions. Later transition to <strong>Vice President, Marketing Strategy and Sales Channel Development</strong>. In this role, was responsible for sustaining and growing the <strong>Company’s $40 billion top line revenue</strong> and developing strong linkages between marketing strategy and channel execution through collaborative alignment between Marketing and Sales.</p>\n<p>Recruited by <strong>Raines International</strong> to a Multibillion-dollar<strong> Energy Retailer</strong> to serve as <strong>Vice President, Head of Commercial Services</strong>. In this role, he is responsible for driving marketing, advertising, product management, business development and customer experience strategies, delivering results in line with company objectives while ensuring business excellence and people leadership across all personnel and business partners.</p>\n<p><strong>Next Move?</strong></p>\n<p>Divisional President or Chief Operating Officer</p>\n",
