      "title": "Director, Channel Strategy &amp; Management, Multibillion-dollar Technology/Insurance Company",
      "URL": "https://rainesinternational.wordpress.com/2015/05/26/director-channel-strategy-management-multibillion-dollar-technologyinsurance-company/",
      "short_URL": "http://wp.me/p7C5yw-291",
      "content": "<p>Received a <strong>Bachelor of Science in Finance</strong>, followed by an <strong>MBA</strong> from <strong>Northwestern University’s Kellogg School of Management.</strong></p>\n<p>Began his career at a <strong>Fortune 50 Electronic Manufacturing Company’s</strong> Financial Management Program, spending to years in multiple roles across finance functions in different business units. Later joined a leading <strong>Fortune 500 Insurance Company</strong>, serving as a <strong>Finance Product Leader</strong>. In this role, was responsible for managing the financial planning, forecasting, and analysis activities for <strong>$1B product line</strong>.</p>\n<p>Moved to a top-tier management consulting firm, leading projects in the company’s strategy, business transformations, and operations practices. Engagements included leading assessment of <strong>$1B acquisition</strong> for a global private equity firm, identifying <strong>$20M in annual cost savings</strong> for a <strong>Fortune 100 CPG Company’s</strong> national sales organization, and identifying improvements in transportation pricing and policies for <strong>Fortune 100 Chemical Manufacturer’s</strong> distribution operations, yielding <strong>$10M in on-going margin improvement.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Recruited by</strong><strong> </strong><strong>Raines International</strong> to a <strong>Multibillion-dollar Technology/Insurance Company</strong> to serve as <strong>Director, Channel Strategy &amp; Management</strong>. He is responsible for providing independent analyses to assist Client Services (Sales) VP/GMs with creating strategies and providing decision support. As a part of a broader team, responsible for developing and/or supporting projects that drive the expansion, growth and profitability of the Company’s client partners.</p>\n<p><strong>Next Move? </strong>Senior leadership roles within the channel strategy &amp; management function.</p>\n",
      "excerpt": "<p>Received a Bachelor of Science in Finance, followed by an MBA from Northwestern University’s Kellogg School of Management. Began his career at a Fortune 50 Electronic Manufacturing Company’s Financial Management Program, spending to years in multiple roles across finance functions in different business units. Later joined a leading Fortune 500 Insurance Company, serving as a [&hellip;]</p>\n",
