      "content": "<p>Received a<strong> BA in Mathematics</strong> from <strong>Dartmouth University</strong> and joined a <strong>management consulting firm</strong> following graduation, where she specialized in the healthcare industry.</p>\n<p>Obtained her <strong>MBA</strong> from the <strong>Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania</strong>.</p>\n<p>Joined a <strong>top-tier management consulting firm</strong>, working in the <strong>Consumer and Retail Practice</strong>. As an <strong>Associate Principal</strong>, focused on developing and implementing tactical <strong>pricing strategies</strong> for both domestic and international Consumer and Retail clients. Engagements included generating a <strong>100-day turnaround plan</strong> for a domestic Retail Company, developing a <strong>3-year national pricing strategy</strong> for a Consumer Goods Company, and driving a <strong>merchandising transformation</strong> for an international Retail Company.</p>\n<p><strong>Recruited by Raines International</strong> to serve as <strong>Senior Director of Strategic Planning</strong> at a <strong>Multi-Billion Dollar Retail Company</strong>. In this role, she works with key senior executives to set the overall strategic priorities of the Company, supporting the development of long-term merchandising initiatives that address the major merchandise issues it is likely to face as it continues to grow.</p>\n<p><strong>Next Move? </strong>Vice President, Strategy or an Operational/Functional leadership role in other areas of the business.</p>\n",
