      "short_URL": "http://wp.me/p7C5yw-297",
      "content": "<p>Received a<strong> Bachelor of Arts </strong>from <strong>Harvard</strong><strong> University</strong> and joined a <strong>top financial services firm</strong><strong>,</strong> working in private wealth management.</p>\n<p>Obtained an <strong>MBA</strong> from the <strong>Wharton School of the University of Pennsylvania</strong>.</p>\n<p>Joined a <strong>top-tier management consulting firm</strong>, working in the <strong>Consumer and Retail Practice</strong>. As an <strong>Associate Principal</strong>, focused on developing and implementing tactical commercial turnaround, growth, and retail finance strategies for both domestic and international <strong>consumer and retail clients</strong>. Engagements included counseling leadership of a <strong>$3bn U.S. CPG</strong> to develop turnaround strategies and partnering with a <strong>$2bn Retail Company</strong> to evaluate growth opportunities.</p>\n<p>Later joined a <strong>Multi-Billion Dollar Wine and Spirits Company</strong> as V<strong>ice President of Planning &amp; Revenue Growth Management</strong>, where he installed new revenue growth practices and led annual planning efforts that contributed to <strong>2.7% net sales/growth</strong> in 2014.</p>\n<p><strong>Recruited by Raines International</strong> to serve as <strong>Vice President</strong><strong> of Strategy</strong> at a <strong>Fortune 500</strong><strong> Retail Company</strong>. Works with key senior executives to set the overall strategic priorities of the Company, supporting the development of long-term merchandising initiatives that address the major merchandise issues it is likely to face as it continues to grow.</p>\n<p><strong>Next Move? </strong>Functional or Operational Leadership Role.</p>\n",
