      "content": "<p>Received a <strong>Bachelor in Mathematics</strong> from <strong>Dartmouth College</strong> and joined a <strong>leading management consulting firm</strong>.</p>\n<p>Following four years of consulting experience, obtained an <strong>MBA</strong> from <strong>MIT’s Sloan School of Management</strong>.</p>\n<p>Later joined the Operations team of a <strong>Fortune 50 Online Retail Company</strong>. Over his eight-year tenure, he served in a variety of Operational roles, ultimately becoming <strong>General Manager and Launch Team Director</strong>. In this senior operational role, he launched more than twenty fulfillment and transportation operations in 2014 across North America and <strong>lead a strategic pilot</strong> for the Company’s North American Operations.</p>\n<p><strong>Recruited by</strong><strong> </strong><strong>Raines International</strong>  to serve as <strong>Vice President of Operations </strong>of a <strong>Multimillion-dollar Consumer Products Company</strong> In this role, he develops and drives all logistics, purchasing, and operations processes of the Company’s warehousing and fulfillment facilities. He works in a strategic and efficient manner that supports a strong operations organization and ensures the Company’s continued growth.</p>\n<p><strong>Next Move?</strong> Chief Operating Officer</p>\n",
