      "short_URL": "http://wp.me/p7C5yw-2aG",
      "content": "<p>Received a <strong>Bachelor of Science </strong>in <strong>Industrial Engineering</strong>, followed by an <strong>MBA</strong> from the <strong>Harvard Business School</strong>.</p>\n<p>Joined a <strong>Fortune 100 Chemical Company</strong> as an <strong>Account Manager</strong>. Engagements included managing strategic relationships with distributors representing <strong>$24M in annual revenue</strong>, coordinating business development activities between the Company and distributor sales teams, and leading a team to resolve daily pricing, delivery, and quality problems at distributor facilities.</p>\n<p>Spent two years at a <strong>top-tier management consulting firm</strong>, where she engaged in a variety of <strong>strategy, operations, and organization initiatives</strong> involving Telecommunications and Informational Technology companies.</p>\n<p>Moved to a <strong>$4B Software Company</strong>, where she served as a <strong>Product and Business Leader</strong>. Defined multi-year roadmaps, requirements, and go-to market strategies including pricing, support models, marketing, and sales that led to the generation of <strong>$100M+ in new revenue</strong> for the Company during her three-year tenure.</p>\n<p><strong>Recruited by Raines International</strong> to a Technology/Insurance Company, where she now serves as <strong>Director of Product Management</strong> for one of the Company’s leading product categories. In this role, she is responsible for developing the overall product strategy and driving the product management practice.</p>\n<p><strong>Next Move?</strong> Senior Director of Product Management</p>\n",
