      "short_URL": "http://wp.me/p7C5yw-29f",
      "content": "<p>Received a <strong>BA</strong> and <strong>MS</strong> in <strong>Computer Science</strong> from <strong>Yale</strong> <strong>and</strong> <strong>Harvard University</strong>, respectively.</p>\n<p>Began his career as a Software Developer at a Healthcare Company before moving to a <strong>Fortune 50 Pharmaceutical Company</strong>. Launched an online consumer behavior modification program that generated <strong>$40M+ in incremental sales</strong> and built partnerships with executives of enterprise IT solutions companies over his four year tenure.</p>\n<p>Earned his <strong>MBA</strong> from <strong>The University of Pennsylvania</strong>, during which he founded an IT Company focused on surveillance solutions. As <strong>Founder and CTO</strong>, led all aspects of financing and structuring of partnerships.</p>\n<p>Joined a <strong>top-tier management consulting firm</strong>. As <strong>Partner</strong>, he focused on enterprise IT transformation across an array of industries. His engagements included driving a <strong>$100M transaction</strong> for a growth equity PE firm, launching a $<strong>450M venture capital fund</strong> for a global healthcare company, and leading a <strong>$50B+ pharmaceutical merger team</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Recruited by Raines International</strong> to the c<strong>onsulting branch of a Private Equity Firm</strong>. As <strong>Director of Information Technology</strong>, he serves as the firm’s technology expert and focuses on technology intensive challenges for investments where IT is a key threshold issue.</p>\n<p><strong>Next Move?</strong> CIO or Senior Role in a Portfolio Company</p>\n",
      "excerpt": "<p>Received a BA and MS in Computer Science from Yale and Harvard University, respectively. Began his career as a Software Developer at a Healthcare Company before moving to a Fortune 50 Pharmaceutical Company. Launched an online consumer behavior modification program that generated $40M+ in incremental sales and built partnerships with executives of enterprise IT solutions [&hellip;]</p>\n",
