      "short_URL": "http://wp.me/p7C5yw-2bk",
      "content": "<p>Spent 3 years in an international role as an Engineer with a <b>Fortune 100 Industrial Manufacturing Company.</b></p>\n<p>Graduated at the top of his class from <b>The Fuqua School of Business.</b></p>\n<p>Spent the next 3 years at a <b>top tier strategy consultancy </b>in the Energy, Chemicals &amp; Utilities practice. His expertise included growth strategy, valuation, post-merger integration, risk analysis, cost reduction, and acquisition readiness support.</p>\n<p><b>Recruited by Raines International</b> to a <b>Director, Strategy &amp; Development</b> role for a<b> Multibillion-dollar Chemicals Company</b> where he works closely with a business unit President and acts as a key resource on issues of strategy development and strategic planning including M&amp;A, strategic alliance, joint ventures, and new product/technology access.</p>\n",
