      "content": "<p>Began his career at a <strong>major investment banking and securities firm</strong> as a <strong>Financial Analyst.</strong></p>\n<p>After 2 years in banking, he graduated in the top 5% of his class with an <strong>MBA</strong> from <strong>Wharton</strong>.</p>\n<p>Spent 10 years at a <strong>top-tier strategy consulting firm</strong> where he co-led the wealth management and insurance practice in the U.S. and Europe. His cases included setting an international asset management expansion strategy for one of Europe’s top mutual fund providers and redesigning the wholesaling organization for a top 10 mutual fund. He left the firm at the <strong>Partner</strong> level.</p>\n<p><strong>Recruited by <strong>Raines International</strong></strong> to a <strong>leading financial advising firm</strong> as the <strong>Senior Vice President of Strategic Planning and Business Development</strong> to lead strategy across a broad range of initiatives creating innovative solutions to complex business issues that have a significant impact on the division’s P&amp;L performance. After 4 years in the role, he was promoted to <strong>President of the division</strong> and <strong>Chief Strategy Officer</strong>.</p>\n<p><strong>Next Move?</strong> Chief Executive Officer</p>\n",
