      "title": "Director, Global Strategy, Multimillion-dollar Industrial Manufacturing Company",
      "URL": "https://rainesinternational.wordpress.com/2012/12/04/director-global-strategy-multimillion-dollar-industrial-manufacturing-company/",
      "short_URL": "http://wp.me/p7C5yw-2bc",
      "content": "<p>Graduated first in his class with a <strong>Bachelor of Chemical Engineering.</strong></p>\n<p>Spent seven years at a <strong>leading Specialty Chemical Manufacturer </strong>where he began his career in engineering and later moved into a production manager role responsible for operations management and supply chain execution.</p>\n<p>Obtained his <strong>MBA </strong>from <strong>The University of Texas at Austin.</strong></p>\n<p>Spent his first two years post–MBA at a<strong> Fortune 500 Specialty Chemical Manufacturer</strong> where he was tasked with directing the productivity enhancement program for the Supply Chain organization of the firm.</p>\n<p>Moved into the <strong>chemicals and energy practice</strong> of a <strong>leading</strong> <strong>strategy consultancy</strong> where he led due diligence for a integrated chemical company’s purchase of a multi-billion dollar manufacturer.</p>\n<p><strong>Recruited by Raines International </strong>as the <strong>Director, Global Strategy</strong> of a <strong>Multimillion-dollar Industrial Manufacturing Company</strong> responsible for developing and monitoring the long term strategic plan. His role includes determining global pricing policies, managing change projects, reviewing potential acquisitions, and supporting due diligence activities.</p>\n<p><strong>Next Move? </strong>Vice President Strategy / Corporate Development</p>\n",
