      "title": "Vice President, Retail Merchandising, Fortune 100 Retail Company",
      "URL": "https://rainesinternational.wordpress.com/2012/12/04/vice-president-retail-merchandising-fortune-100-retail-company/",
      "short_URL": "http://wp.me/p7C5yw-2aO",
      "content": "<p>Obtained his <strong>MBA</strong> from <strong>The Wharton School</strong>.</p>\n<p>Spent the next 15 years at a <strong>top-tier strategy consultancy</strong> where he ascended to the <strong>Partner</strong> level in the Retail Pricing practice. In this role, his expertise included merchandise planning, category management, operating model development, pricing &amp; promotion optimization, customer insight &amp; segmentation, and analytics. He served as an advisor to a variety of senior executives at many Fortune 200 Retail Companies during his tenure at the firm.</p>\n<p><strong>Recruited by Raines International </strong>to a <strong>Fortune 100 Retail Company</strong> as the <strong>Vice President of Retail Merchandising</strong> for a $4 billion segment. He heads the merchandising strategy and direction to ensure the implementation of said strategy, working on all facets of the P&amp;L including sales, margin, and expense reduction.</p>\n<p><strong>Next move? </strong>Chief Merchant, General Manager</p>\n",
