      "title": "Director, Corporate Strategy &amp; Development, Multibillion-dollar Chemicals Company",
      "URL": "https://rainesinternational.wordpress.com/2012/09/19/director-corporate-strategy-development-multibillion-dollar-chemicals-company/",
      "short_URL": "http://wp.me/p7C5yw-2be",
      "content": "<p>Earned his <strong>Bachelor and Master of Science in Civil Engineering</strong> and moved into a <strong>Project Manager</strong> role at an <strong>Engineering and Environmental Consulting firm</strong> where he managed multiple engagements in energy operations and regulatory compliance for major chemical and manufacturing companies.</p>\n<p>Received his <strong>MBA </strong>from <strong>The Fuqua School of Business.</strong></p>\n<p>Spend the next 4 years at a <strong>leading strategy consulting firm</strong> where he focused on mergers and acquisitions. He led multiple engagements including corporate development strategy, synergy valuation, deal due-diligence, and post-merger planning for complex deals.</p>\n<p><strong>Recruited by Raines International</strong> to be the <strong>Director of Corporate Strategy &amp; Development </strong>for a <strong>Multibillion-dollar Chemicals Company </strong>where he works directly with the segment President and acts as a key resource on issues of strategy development and strategic planning including M&amp;A, strategic alliances, joint ventures, and new technology access.</p>\n<p><strong>Next Move?</strong> Business Unit General Manager</p>\n",
