      "title": "Vice President, Pricing, Fortune 200 Service Company",
      "URL": "https://rainesinternational.wordpress.com/2012/03/19/vice-president-pricing-fortune-200-service-company/",
      "short_URL": "http://wp.me/p7C5yw-29X",
      "content": "<p>Began his career at a <strong>Big 4 Accounting Firm</strong> in London.</p>\n<p>Held roles from analyst to<strong> Senior Director</strong> in the <strong>pricing department</strong> at a <strong>Computer Manufacturing Company</strong>. His heavy focus on pricing strategies included designing and deploying a global price band strategy.</p>\n<p>Attended <strong>Kellogg School of Management </strong>and received his <strong>MBA</strong> during his tenure at the manufacturing company<strong>.</strong></p>\n<p>Spent 4 years post MBA at <strong>a top-tier strategy consulting firm</strong> as a <strong>pricing expert</strong> responsible for leading the firm and client teams to identify the highest impact pricing areas of opportunity and designing practical solutions. He worked on a variety of engagements including designing a performance management infrastructure for an airline client as well as executing a cross-business unit pricing transformation program for a tech conglomerate.</p>\n<p><strong>Recruited out of management consulting by <strong>Raines International</strong> </strong>to be the <strong>Vice President of Pricing</strong> for a <strong>Fortune 200 Service Company</strong>. He is responsible for rebuilding the Pricing strategy for the newly restructured company and defining a compelling Pricing vision and roadmap that will help grow revenue and market share.</p>\n<p><strong>Next Move?</strong> Chief Marketing Officer</p>\n",
      "excerpt": "<p>Began his career at a Big 4 Accounting Firm in London. Held roles from analyst to Senior Director in the pricing department at a Computer Manufacturing Company. His heavy focus on pricing strategies included designing and deploying a global price band strategy. Attended Kellogg School of Management and received his MBA during his tenure at [&hellip;]</p>\n",
